  "body": "For some reason PoS header downloader doesn't download any headers, resulting in timeouts. Something like:\r\n```\r\n[INFO] [12-14|11:39:37.003] [Downloader] Downloaded PoS Headers      now=25443063 blk/sec=0.000\r\n[WARN] [12-14|11:40:03.120] [Downloader] Timeout                     requestId=29 peerID=d647316f9edb58608cd11ce59730446af08a78c04563863602405a334607ef2ca745a5a4cc8a62570d5ba7460b5cf9543ca3f6871319d784595c3e7e6afc3100\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1) Run erigon with `--chain=gnosis` (use the latest `devel` in order to pick up PR #6306).\r\n2) Run a CL. Here are instructions for Lighthouse:\r\na) Build lighthouse from the stable branch (>=[v3.3.0](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/releases/tag/v3.3.0)) with `FEATURES=gnosis make`. Refer to the full instruction at https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/installation-source.html.\r\nb) Run lighthouse with `lighthouse bn --network gnosis --execution-endpoint=http://127.0.0.1:8551 --checkpoint-sync-url=https://checkpoint.gnosis.gateway.fm --execution-jwt=<erigon_data_dir>/jwt.hex`\r\nc) You might also need to add `--boot-nodes` to lighthouse â€“ see https://docs.gnosischain.com/updates/20221208-temporary-bootnodes.\r\n\r\n#### Related Issues\r\nIssue #5456 and perhaps #6307.",
